> Re: HORSES - CAN I RIDE OR NOT ?</span><hr size=1> You can buy them in the Bazaar. But they are very expensive. (10k for the basic model - no speed bonus, to 100k for the bard-speed horse) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustina1701.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stina1701</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 11:29:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1182.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HORSES - CAN I RIDE OR NOT ?</span><hr size=1> Yes you can ride. But you need lots of plats to buy one. Also have to have Shadows of Luclin installed and the Horse graphics marked. The reason you cant see many on horses is the horrific price you have to pay to get one.<br><br>Stina1701 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukelisk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, YOU'RE evil</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 5:36:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1182.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HORSES - CAN I RIDE OR NOT ?</span><hr size=1> Actually, Voskor, the 100k horse goes nowhere near the speed of a mid-level bard with a decent drum. It goes not go cheetah speed, either.  The 100k horse is said to run about 1.5 times the speed of a normal SoW. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 7:02:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1182.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HORSES - CAN I RIDE OR NOT ?</span><hr size=1> Verant posted recently about horses....<br><br>They made it clear that the addition of horses is supposed to be seen as a luxury status symbol -- it is something that only the wealthy and successful high level players can afford. <br><br>Owning a horse in Norrath has the real life equivalent of wearing a Rolex on your wrist or a millionare owning his/her own personal yacht. <br><br>This is pretty much how I interpret what Verant stated. <br><br>That said..... it will be some time until many players can afford horses on this server. This is still a young server, and the vast majority of characters are likely below level 25.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 479<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 7:04:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1182.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HORSES - CAN I RIDE OR NOT ?</span><hr size=1>    I think they should add a really cheap, broken down horse, that maybe has crooked teeth and is cross-eyed, and moves at the same speed a level 1 rogue does while sneaking, that only costs 50 plat or so, just so people who don't go all out for the end-game can afford one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 324<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 7:16:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1182.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HORSES - CAN I RIDE OR NOT ?</span><hr size=1> I think it's ridiculous.  Sure, I want one.  But how come they couldn't have given a more UO style of having mounts.  I really want one, but I doubt I'll ever have one because I can't see wasting that amount of money unless I'm in the extreme high-end game and have all the gear that I'll ever need.  Otherwise I'll hold onto my money and buy anything I may want.  Or I'll drop by Freeport and put 1000pp on each rat. <p><center><font size=+2><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bmaidensfancy">Shiden Kaidan</a></font><br>Tier'dal Knight<br><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/"> Firiona Vie</a><br><font size=1><font color=red>@}</font><font color=green>--,--'---- </font></font><br><i>"May you walk the halls of Hate unblinded."</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 481<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 8:41:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1182.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HORSES - CAN I RIDE OR NOT ?</span><hr size=1>    My only guess is that the insanely high predator (bear, hill giant, tiger, lion, etc) to prey (horses, newbies) ratio has left horses an endagered creature, and only the extremely wealthy can afford one.<br><br>- Syll<br><br>PS: I agree it's ridiculous. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=1155.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1182.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.firiona-vie.com/images/arfv.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=1182.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1182.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1182.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionaviefrm10">A Bard for a Day<option value="firionaviefrm23">Hero Heart Tavern<option value="firionaviefrm15">The Polling Boot